rComments: POL1020 Excellent pédagogue. Nétudiez que les concepts importants (Papillon indique clairement lesquels le sont). Préparez vos questions à développement en avance ( vous saurez quels concepts seront à lexamen). Les évaluations sont excessivement punitives, donc demander à votre moniteur/trice ses attentes en avance. Bonne chance, ça va bien aller

ses auxiliaires sont des correcteurs bien trop sévère pour des élèves débutant dans la matière. Le cours est facile mais la correction vous fera vite changer d'avis. dommage pour un prof qui est tres interessant
Love this teacher. Intersting class. Il connait très bien sa matière!  Not so easy, but ok.
très interessant, il rend son cours passionnant et interactif

Martin Papillon is a great professor. He's very thorough and has very clear notes. I'd point out that attending is class is almost a must as he doesn't always complete his powerpoints and does give tips on what to study for the exams.  His exams can be a little tricky but nothing too hard. However his graders are ridiculously strict.

Le professeur est assez claire sur la matière, il est très facile de le comprendre.   Je regrette une seule chose : son mauvais choix dans ses correcteurs. Des correcteurs qui te corrigent et se contredisent dans le même devoir. PIRE CORRECTEURS EVER. Monsieur Papillon changez vos correcteurs !!!!!!
unbiased, very knowledgable prof, especially on aboriginal matters, guest lecturers were also very welcome! Would recommend

Offers an objective view to Canadian Politics. Brings in guest speakers from all parties, which always makes for a more interesting discussion. 3 Assignments, a midterm and a final - all very clear and fairly graded. I would take another class from him!

Overall, great prof. Interesting and engaging lectures, which are consistently tied to the situation of democracy in Canada. Midterm and exam was easy, and consisted of identify and explain, and essay questions. Assignments consisted of 3 short papers, or a 30 hour volunteering placement which provides great experience. I would strongly recommend this prof.

awesome prof, knows his stuff. gets off topic and doesn`t always finish his lectures but he makes up for it. and gives you guest lectures. ALSO, gives you many assignments to get marked on, so your average can be fixed if you mess uo on one thing!

Funny and cute. He's very clear and his notes are great. Problem is his contradiction. Says certain things will be on/not be on the test, and that turns out to be false. Easy going and approachable. He's not intimidating and you won't feel nervous going up to him and asking questions
Really great prof! Interesting lectures, good assignments (a variety of things to make up grade), guest speaker - all in all, a good experience.

He was really into the subject but he constantly contradicted himself. He once said that he wanted personal definitions on the mid-term then he criticized the class for making their answers not enough like the text book. His thick French accent also made him hard to understand sometimes. Overall a sub-par prof.

Great prof!  Enjoyed all of his classes so far and he puts effort into making sure that the material is relevant to student interests.  He focuses on stories that have resonance and although English is likely his second language, he's still very clear.  You probably don't have to attend all of the  classes but they're pretty enjoyable, go anyway!
Excellent Professor! You can tell he cares deeply about the subject and knows it well. If you work as hard as he does you will do really well!

This class was really interesting and I recommend it for anyone with an interest in politics and the pertinent theories.  I had trouble following the class for the first while, but the TAs were SO helpful, the prof is really nice, and his exam outline really helped to trim the course and structure the content.  I want him back!

Good class. His lectures were at times boring...I skipped lots of classes and didn't read the text book and still got a B+. You need to read the additional texts because they were on the exam. He is helpful with mid-term and exam review. Overall a good class.
Very engaging prof. As said, he keeps current with the topics that are taught, relating it to modern issues and throwing in some good puns to keep it interesting. Will take another course again.

Papillon is hilarious and probably one of the most likeable profs I've had so far. Lectures are kept very interesting, and he links everything to present-day politics. Very funny prof, the humor make the subject at hand a little less dry. Is French-speaking but this is hardly noticeable when he speaks English.
